    High-quality cement retailers in the UK include
    CEMEX UK, Tarmac (which owns the Blue Circle brand), and Heidelberg Materials UK. These are all major manufacturers that produce a range of cement products, from bulk supply to bagged options for various uses, including those for both trade professionals and DIYers. 
    • CEMEX UK: A major cement manufacturer with a significant presence in the UK.
    • Tarmac: Owns the well-known and trusted Blue Circle brand, celebrating 125 years of innovation in cementitious materials, as reported by Tarmac.
    • Heidelberg Materials UK: A leading manufacturer of both bulk and bagged cement, as well as other building materials like low-carbon cement replacements (Regen GGBS), notes this Heidelberg Materials page.
    • Breedon: A major UK cement manufacturer with one of the largest cement plants in the UK, located in Derbyshire.

    What are the cement companies in the UK?
    An AI Overview is not available for this searchCan't generate an AI overview right now. Try again later.
    AI Overview
    Major cement companies in the UK include Cemex UK, Tarmac (Blue Circle), Hanson Cement, and Breedon Cement, which are among the dominant players in the industry. Other companies like Heidelberg Materials UK also manufacture and supply cement and related products.
     
    Major UK cement companies
    • Cemex UK:
      Supplies bagged and bulk cement and operates a network of plants across the country. 
    • Tarmac:
      The company's Blue Circle brand is a leading cement brand in the UK, providing products for various applications from infrastructure projects to DIY. 
    • Hanson Cement:
      Offers a wide range of cement products, including Portland Cement and White Portland Cement, along with GGBS and Fly Ash. 
    • Breedon Cement:
      A key producer of cement and other construction materials in Great Britain and Ireland, with its Hope Cement Plant in Derbyshire being the UK's largest. 
    • Heidelberg Materials UK:
      Produces cement in bulk and bags, along with low-carbon alternatives like GGBS and captured carbon cement. 
    Other companies
    • Aggregate Industries UK: One of the four large companies that dominate the industry, as noted by IBISWorld. 
    • SpecifiedBy: Lists over 10 manufacturers, including Fermacell, Mapei UK, and Bostik, alongside the major players. 
    • Ecocem: Also listed by SpecifiedBy as a UK cement manufacturer.

      How to identify good quality cement?
      RUB TEST: In this test, one must take a little cement between their fingers and rub it. If the texture feels smooth, it's considered good quality cement. If the texture is rough, it is likely adulterated with sand.
